form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: NOTICE OF HEARING IN DEPORTATION PROCEEDINGS, 1-250/1-389 DUE BY

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/28/2023 UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE EXECUTIVE OFFICE FOR IMMIGRATION REVIEW OFFICE OF THE IMMIGRATION JUDGE P. 0. BOX 2326 SAN FRANCISCO, CA 94126-2320 DATE: 8.25.89 A# 128-749-267 TO: The Respondent RE: Solis- Rumeio, Marcline NOTICE OF HEARING IN DEPORTATION PROCEEDINGS PLEASE TAKE NOTICE THAT THE ABOVE-CAPTIONED CASE WILL BE CONDUCTED BY AN IMMIGRATION JUDGE ON November 14, 1989 AT THE OFFICE OF THE IMMIGRATION JUDGE, ROOM 404, 630 SANSOME STREET, SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIA 94111 AT 1:00pm ( REGULAR / MASTER ). NOTE: YOU MAY BE REPRESENTED IN THIS PROCEEDING, AT NO EXPENSE TO THE GOVERNMENT BY AN ATTORNEY OR OTHER INDIVIDUAL AUTHORIZED AND QUALIFIED TO REPRESENT PERSONS BEFORE AN IMMIGRATION JUDGE. IF Y U WISH TO BE SO REPRESENTED, YOUR ATTORNEY OR REPRESENTATIVE SHOULD APPEAR WITH YOU AT THE HEARING. FAILURE TO APPEAR AT YOUR HEARING MAY RESULT IN ANY OR ALL OF THE FOLLOWING: 1. FORFEITURE OF YOUR BOND, 2. YOUR HEARING BEING HEARD IN YOUR ABSENCE UNDER sec. 242(B) OF THE IMMIGRATION AND NATIONALITY ACT, 3. AN ORDER OF DEPORTATION BEING ENTERED AGAINST YOU, 4. ISSUANCE OF A WARRANT FOR YOUR ARREST AND DEPORTATION. 1-256/1-589 DUE BY OFFICE OF THE IMMIGRATION JUDGE Naver Kritzman BY: LOIR CLERK cc. Trial Attorney
